{"questionId":"21249","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graph shows the variation with temperature <em>T</em> of the pressure <em>P</em> of a fixed mass of helium&nbsp;gas trapped in a container with a fixed volume of 1.0 × 10<sup>−3 </sup>m<sup>3</sup>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/b1d5c09d162469f452949aef01fd4bc17a796dbd.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Deduce whether helium behaves as an ideal gas over the temperature range 250 K&nbsp;to 500 K.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«He behaves as ideal gas if»&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>∝</mo><mi>T</mi></math>&nbsp;«at constant V»&nbsp;<strong>✓</strong></p>\n<p>uses two points to show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>∝</mo><mi>T</mi></math>&nbsp;<strong>✓</strong></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>MP1</strong> can also be described as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>p</mi><mi>T</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">OR&nbsp;</mtext><mfrac><mi>p</mi><mi>T</mi></mfrac><mtext>=</mtext><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac></math></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"21249","referenceCode":"21M.2.SL.TZ2.2a","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce whether helium behaves as an ideal gas over the temperature range 250 K to 500 K.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics","3.2 – Modelling a gas","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}